04/05/2005
ATHENS, Greece -- Prime Minister Costas Karamanlis and Foreign Minister Petros Molyviatis met on Tuesday (3 May) to discuss foreign policy, ahead of Karamanlis' trip to Washington later this month.
The three main subjects were Cyprus, the name dispute with Skopje and bilateral relations with Turkey.
Also Tuesday, a Russian government and business delegation wrapped up a five-day visit to Greece.
Efforts to boost economic ties include the launch of direct flights between Russia and northern Greece during the coming summer tourist season.
(ANA, MPA, ET1 - 04/05/05)
